==Continuity==
The series' final novel, ''Prophets of the Dark Side'', ends with [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] walking down the aisle of their wedding ceremony, but a [[Retroactive continuity|retcon]] states that the wedding was interrupted and never completed. Han and Leia were again [[Wedding of Han Solo and Leia Organa/Legends|married]] in the later novel ''[[The Courtship of Princess Leia]]'' ([[1994]]), by [[Dave Wolverton]].

A [[Retroactive continuity|retcon]] in [[The Essential Chronology (real-world book)|''The Essential Chronology'']] revealed that Trioculus, Grand Moff [[Bertroff Hissa]], and other members of the [[Central Committee of Grand Moffs]] were trying to overthrow [[Director of Imperial Intelligence]] [[Ysanne Isard]]&mdash;who ruled the galactic capital of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]]&mdash;and usurp control of the Empire. Grand Moff Hissa connived to install Trioculus as the public leader of the Empire and gain support from the majority of the Imperials loyal to Isard.

A retcon in the unlicensed [[Polyhedron 103]] magazine stated that the ''Jedi Prince'' series had in fact been a children's story of the actual events told by [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] to her children [[Darth Caedus|Jacen]], [[Jaina Solo Fel|Jaina]], and [[Anakin Solo|Anakin]]. However, this retcon was later ignored in ''[[The Dark Side Sourcebook]]'' which retconned the story to be true, but with numerous fixes&mdash;one of the most prominent, that the Kadann featured in the series was a con artist hired by [[Imperial Intelligence/Legends|Imperial Intelligence]] and the Prophets of the Dark Side were pretenders working for the [[Church of the Dark Side]]. The original Kadann never appeared in the novels, and the true Prophets of the Dark Side were hiding on [[Bosthirda/Legends|Bosthirda]] during the events of the series. ''[[Who's Who: Imperial Grand Admirals]]'' established that the false Kadann met his end after [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Afsheen Makati]]&mdash;who hated the true Kadann&mdash;mistakenly thought that the pretender was the Supreme Prophet of the Dark Side and destroyed [[Scardia Station]], killing the false Kadann.

The origins of Triclops were revealed in [[Aliens in the Empire|''Aliens of the Empire'']] by [[Abel G. Peña]] and [[Rich Handley]]. Triclops was not Palpatine's biological son, but the product of a scientific experiment in which Darth Sidious hired scientists [[Mammon Hoole]] and [[Borborygmus Gog]] to study the spontaneous generation of life. [[Sly Moore/Legends|Sly Moore]] obtained a [[Human/Legends|Human]] female called [[Niobi]] as the test subject for the project. Niobi gave birth to a three-eyed mutant, and she and her son were banished by [[Sarcev Quest]], a [[Dark side adept/Legends|Dark Side Adept]] loyal to Emperor Palpatine. However, in [[2013]], Peña and Handley wrote a new series of article for the official [[Star Wars Blog]], entitled ''[[Barely Tolerable: Alien Henchmen of the Empire]]''. In part one of that series, it was revealed that the three-eyed son of Niobi was in fact Trioculus.

In part three of the article series, which was released on [[September 12]], 2013, Handley and Peña finally tied Triclops with Sly Moore, but did not explicitly reveal the father's identity. Later in the year, Peña and [[Greg Mitchell]] co-wrote another blog article titled ''[[The Star Wars Spy Game: SPIN Declassified]]'', which explicitely referred to Triclops as Palpatine's true son, not simply an alleged one.

One conflict that has not been addressed involves the Rebel research center called [[Defense Research and Planetary Assistance Center|DRAPAC]] on [[Mount Yoda]]. According to [[Timothy Zahn]]'s ''[[Heir to the Empire]]'', Leia, Luke's twin sister, didn't even know where Luke had been training during the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']]{{'s}} stop at [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] until, after returning from an expedition to [[Dagobah/Legends|Dagobah]] five years after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]]&mdash;well after the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] had been established on Coruscant&mdash;Luke confided where Yoda's [[Yoda's Hut/Legends|secret retreat]] had been.

